==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plod
<hw>Plod</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Plodded</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Plodding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Gf. Gael. <ets>plod</ets> a
clod, a pool; also, to strike or pelt with a clod or clods.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To travel slowly but steadily; to trudge.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To toil; to drudge; especially, to study laboriously
and patiently.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Plodding</xex> schoolmen.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plod</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plod
<hw>Plod</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To walk on slowly or
heavily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ploughman homeward <qex>plods</qex> his weary way.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plodder</ent>⟦br⟧
